questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue in a high-throughput Spring Boot application. A component dynamically loads custom business logic rules from external directories using a custom `ClassLoader`. Users report intermittent `ClassCastException` errors when executing these rules, even though the loaded class explicitly implements the `com.app.Rule` interface. The implementation looks like this:

java
public class RuleExecutor {
    public void runRule(String path, String className) throws Exception {
        URL[] urls = { new File(path).toURI().toURL() };
        try (URLClassLoader loader = new URLClassLoader(urls)) {
            Class<?> clazz = loader.loadClass(className);
            Rule rule = (Rule) clazz.getDeclaredConstructor().newInstance();
            rule.execute();
        }
    }
}
